The paper deals with the problem of Knowledge Graph Completion (KGC) using limited training instances, which is a common challenge in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed framework utilizes an adversarial procedure, which is a common technique in Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The framework also involves feature learning and transfer learning, which are relevant to Database (cs.DB) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
